{
  "timestamp": "2026-07-01T20:42:48Z",
  "title": "Homepage & Events revamp (Atlas)",
  "type": "feature",
  "userRequest": "# Homepage & Events Revamp — Atlas Direction\n\nIterating on the Harvard in Tech site from HIT-team feedback. Adopt the **Atlas (01)** design and expand the homepage + Events page. *(Editorial (03) was your runner-up.)*\n\n## Design direction — Atlas re-skin (the biggest lift)\nThe implemented site currently uses the **teal Strikingly \"persona\" theme** (a faithful repro of the *original* harvardintech.com: `#0ca5a5` teal, Roboto). Atlas is a different system — **Harvard crimson editorial**: `#A41034` crimson + ink/paper palette, Helvetica Neue + Times serif + JetBrains Mono. Adopting it re-skins `tokens.css`, `BaseLayout`, and every section.\n\n## Homepage (`src/pages/index.astro`) — target structure\n1. **Menu** — full mega-menu from your doc: **Programs** (All Events · Webinars · Podcasts) · **Chapters** (Boston & Cambridge · NYC · London · DC & DMV · Seattle) · **Communities** (WhatsApp) · **Content Hub** (Blog · Medium · Substack · LinkedIn) · **Membership** (About→Mission/Board · Get Involved→Volunteer · Support→Donate/Sponsorship). *(Header currently renders only single-level dropdowns → needs a grouped mega-menu rework.)*\n2. **Sliding Hero banner** — carousel with button-link CTAs (replaces the static hero).\n3. **Stats** — new band (members · chapters · events · cities); values editable via settings.\n4. **Upcoming Events** — existing, re-skinned.\n5. **Our Chapters** — new landing section surfacing the 5 chapters.\n6. **Focus Areas** — new; cards for the main program categories (Programs, Chapters, Communities, Content Hub, Membership).\n7. **Content Hub** — new; Blog · Medium · Substack · LinkedIn.\n8. **Board of Directors** — existing, re-skinned.\n9. **Bring HIT to your city** — existing `GetInvolved` section; already has a **Volunteer** button (keep + re-skin).\n10. **Giving Campaign** — new section (from doc).\n11. **Footer** — re-skin + add **LinkedIn** (no LinkedIn icon exists yet → add asset + `socialIcon` mapping).\n12. **Logo** — swap in your new logo files *(pending — I still need those files)*.\n\n## Events page (`src/pages/events.astro` / `EventsPage.astro`)\nRework toward the HBSWA reference (structured events listing) + **Luma integration** (calendar embed, reusing the existing `EmbedForm` iframe pattern).\n\n## Content change\nReplace the current chapters (Japan / SF / LA / NYC) with **Boston & Cambridge · NYC · London · DC & DMV · Seattle** — each with Board/Committee members + Events. Updates chapter markdown, `nav.json`, and chapter scenarios/routes.\n\n## Scenarios (data states — production DB starts empty)\n- **Empty** (day-one default): hero + section shells with graceful empty states.\n- **Sparse**: a couple of events, a few chapters.\n- **Rich**: full events, all 5 chapters, full board, content-hub items — exercises carousel, grids, stats.\n- **Edge cases**: long event titles, missing images, a chapter with no upcoming events; Events page with the Luma embed present.\n- Re-capture the existing `/` and `/events` app scenarios + ~10 landing component scenarios after the re-skin.\n\n## Explicitly deferred to later iterations\nLogin / SSO / Harvard Key · Google Analytics · SEO/AEO · site-wide Custom HTML/iFrame blocks. *(The Events Luma embed is included here.)*\n\n**Mode:** UI (heavy UI work).",
  "description": "Redesigned the Harvard in Tech site to the board-approved Atlas direction: a Harvard-crimson editorial system with a utility bar + taxonomy mega-menu (Programs / Chapters / Communities / Content Hub / Membership), a sliding hero carousel, a stats band, and an editorial section stack (Our Chapters, Focus Areas, Content Hub, Board of Directors, Get Involved, Giving Campaign, WhatsApp, Support, Gallery, Contact) plus an Events page that embeds/links the live Luma calendar. Replaced the five chapters with Boston & Cambridge / NYC / London / DC & DMV / Seattle, added a LinkedIn social + icon, and switched to real-data-only null states (removed placeholder events; the empty Upcoming Events state offers Subscribe-to-Luma and newsletter CTAs). Corrected accuracy (Est. 2013, real Content Hub links, removed the fabricated fundraising meter). Reused the tested initials/formatEventDate helpers, registered 9 new component scenarios, and recaptured all touched sections/pages to the new styling.",
